00:36:53.630 --> 00:36:56.120
first openly gay
ambassador in America

00:36:56.120 --> 00:36:57.520
ever to be an ambassador.

00:36:57.520 --> 00:37:01.790
And now we have like seven,
or we did until Trump.

00:37:01.790 --> 00:37:05.480
Anyway, so I don't
say this because I

00:37:05.480 --> 00:37:06.840
get a commission on it.

00:37:06.840 --> 00:37:09.510
And I don't want a job.

00:37:09.510 --> 00:37:12.690
But I actually believe,
biased though I might be,

00:37:12.690 --> 00:37:15.230
that actually to
support Democrats,

00:37:15.230 --> 00:37:16.640
or to run for
office, but I don't

00:37:16.640 --> 00:37:21.530
want to have you leave Google
before your option's best.

00:37:21.530 --> 00:37:23.360
To run for office
would be great.

00:37:23.360 --> 00:37:25.130
To support friends
and people that

00:37:25.130 --> 00:37:27.740
inspire you to run for office
would be great, especially

00:37:27.740 --> 00:37:30.824
in places that are purple.

00:37:30.824 --> 00:37:32.240
If you get a chance
to be assigned

00:37:32.240 --> 00:37:34.406
to North Carolina for Google
or something like that,

00:37:34.406 --> 00:37:38.180
we need your vote there, not
quite so much in New York.

00:37:38.180 --> 00:37:45.980
But to be involved in politics,
and to be respectful of people

00:37:45.980 --> 00:37:48.050
who don't agree with us.

00:37:48.050 --> 00:37:53.120
Hillary, at last year's dinner,
I was as far from Hillary as I

00:37:53.120 --> 00:37:57.350
am from you, [INAUDIBLE],,
when she said--

00:37:57.350 --> 00:37:58.730
she had pneumonia.

00:37:58.730 --> 00:38:00.630
We didn't know it at the time.

00:38:00.630 --> 00:38:03.250
But that was that period
she had pneumonia.

00:38:03.250 --> 00:38:04.700
And she was with friends--

00:38:04.700 --> 00:38:08.320
granted 800 friends, and there
was press there, I guess,

00:38:08.320 --> 00:38:09.900
and so she shouldn't
have said this.

00:38:09.900 --> 00:38:13.361
But she said that thing about
the basket of the deplorables,

00:38:13.361 --> 00:38:15.110
that half the people
voting for Trump are,

00:38:15.110 --> 00:38:18.140
and the other half are--

00:38:18.140 --> 00:38:20.420
it was a dumb and
unfortunate thing to say.

00:38:20.420 --> 00:38:23.000
And even that little thing--
there were much bigger factors,

00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:26.930
but that alone might have been
enough to change the thing.

00:38:26.930 --> 00:38:32.120
But with a few exceptions--
obviously virulent racists are

00:38:32.120 --> 00:38:33.290
deplorable--

00:38:33.290 --> 00:38:36.860
but most people who voted
for Trump are not deplorable.

00:38:36.860 --> 00:38:38.630
They were bamboozled.

00:38:38.630 --> 00:38:43.640
And we need to talk to them with
respect, which they deserve,

00:38:43.640 --> 00:38:48.680
and not tell them that they're
idiots, which they're not.

00:38:48.680 --> 00:38:52.010
But they have sure been fooled
by Rush Limbaugh and Glenn Beck

00:38:52.010 --> 00:38:55.040
and Fox News and Roger Ailes--

00:38:55.040 --> 00:38:58.090
I'm not even sure how much
peace he should rest in--

00:38:58.090 --> 00:39:03.410
and Trump, who has
told us, not only

00:39:03.410 --> 00:39:05.190
are we going to get
tired of winning.

00:39:05.190 --> 00:39:06.190
I mean, we're going to
be winning so much we're

00:39:06.190 --> 00:39:07.750
going to get tired of winning.

00:39:07.750 --> 00:39:11.479
We are going to have great
health care, as I guess all

00:39:11.479 --> 00:39:12.770
you do because we're at Google.

00:39:12.770 --> 00:39:17.200
But great health care,
not for the same price.

00:39:17.200 --> 00:39:19.290
Everybody's going to
have great health care.

00:39:19.290 --> 00:39:23.040
And not just less,
at a fraction--

00:39:23.040 --> 00:39:26.770
nay-- and how often you hear
nay anymore, other than a horse?

00:39:26.770 --> 00:39:29.540
Nay, at a tiny
fraction of the cost.

00:39:29.540 --> 00:39:30.510
These are his words.

00:39:30.510 --> 00:39:32.135
You are going to have
great health care

00:39:32.135 --> 00:39:34.520
at a tiny fraction of the cost.

00:39:34.520 --> 00:39:37.200
It's 1933 all over again.

00:39:37.200 --> 00:39:39.770
How many of you
know that Trump kept

00:39:39.770 --> 00:39:43.400
a book of Hitler's speeches
by his bedside for years?

00:39:43.400 --> 00:39:44.579
Nobody, it's amazing.

00:39:44.579 --> 00:39:46.620
So my friend Marie Brenner
wrote a profile of him

00:39:46.620 --> 00:39:49.530
for "Vanity Fair" about
17 or 18 years ago.

00:39:49.530 --> 00:39:54.000
And his ex-wife,
Ivana, told her that.

00:39:54.000 --> 00:39:54.881
And she said, what?

00:39:54.881 --> 00:39:56.380
He kept a book of
Hitler's speeches?

00:39:56.380 --> 00:39:56.875
What?

00:39:56.875 --> 00:39:58.830
She said, yeah, it's in my
divorce attorney's safe.

00:39:58.830 --> 00:39:59.910
You want to see the book?

00:39:59.910 --> 00:40:03.624
And so she goes to Donald--

00:40:03.624 --> 00:40:05.040
and by the way, I
call him Donald.

00:40:05.040 --> 00:40:07.320
I have friends
who golf with him.

00:40:07.320 --> 00:40:08.810
I have friends who--

00:40:08.810 --> 00:40:12.380
one of his bankers
is a friend of mine.

00:40:12.380 --> 00:40:16.080
When he was just Donald
Trump, OK, not my cup of tea,

00:40:16.080 --> 00:40:17.750
but go ahead.

00:40:17.750 --> 00:40:19.270
Be Donald Trump.

00:40:19.270 --> 00:40:21.290
But to run the world?

00:40:21.290 --> 00:40:21.840
No.

00:40:21.840 --> 00:40:25.020
So anyway, Maria goes to
Donald and says, what?

00:40:25.020 --> 00:40:25.650
Is this true?

00:40:25.650 --> 00:40:28.580
You have a book of Hitler's
speeches by your bedside?

00:40:28.580 --> 00:40:30.300
And he got all defensive.

00:40:30.300 --> 00:40:32.449
He said, well,
first of all, Marie,

00:40:32.449 --> 00:40:33.990
it's not a book of
Hitler's speeches.

00:40:33.990 --> 00:40:35.940
It's "Mein Kampf."

00:40:35.940 --> 00:40:36.570
OK, great.

00:40:36.570 --> 00:40:39.090
You've got "Mein Kampf"
by your bedside, OK.

00:40:39.090 --> 00:40:42.870
And second, it was a
gift to me by the head

00:40:42.870 --> 00:40:45.060
of Paramount Pictures, a
Hollywood movie studio,

00:40:45.060 --> 00:40:46.410
and he's Jewish.

00:40:46.410 --> 00:40:48.710
So give me a break, Marie.

00:40:48.710 --> 00:40:50.610
So Marie goes to
Marty Davis, who

00:40:50.610 --> 00:40:52.840
is the head of Paramount
Pictures at the time.

00:40:52.840 --> 00:40:57.430
He's since met his ward.

00:40:57.430 --> 00:40:59.830
And what about it, Marty?

00:40:59.830 --> 00:41:01.840
As so Marty says,
well, first of all,

00:41:01.840 --> 00:41:04.440
even though it doesn't
matter, and even

00:41:04.440 --> 00:41:09.330
though I do run a Hollywood
studio, I'm not Jewish.

00:41:09.330 --> 00:41:11.610
And second, no, it
wasn't "Mein Kampf."

00:41:11.610 --> 00:41:17.140
It's a book of Hitler's
speeches called "My New Order."

00:41:17.140 --> 00:41:18.630
So, A, that's true.

00:41:18.630 --> 00:41:20.850
And B, I went on after I--

00:41:20.850 --> 00:41:23.755
and "Vanity Fair" then
republished all this last year.

00:41:23.755 --> 00:41:25.796
And it was in "Vanity
Fair," and I wrote about it

00:41:25.796 --> 00:41:28.500
about 1,000 times in my
column, which six people read.

00:41:28.500 --> 00:41:31.820
Thank you and you and you.

00:41:31.820 --> 00:41:33.730
It was seven until
my mom passed on.

00:41:33.730 --> 00:41:36.300
But anyway, so, I mean,
it's been out there,

00:41:36.300 --> 00:41:38.406
and some people know this.

00:41:38.406 --> 00:41:41.402
And by the way, if you're like
the head of marketing for P&amp;G

00:41:41.402 --> 00:41:43.110
or something, that's
an interesting thing

00:41:43.110 --> 00:41:44.970
to have by your bedside,
because how do you

00:41:44.970 --> 00:41:47.730
influence mass psychology,
and how do you--

00:41:47.730 --> 00:41:49.470
OK?

00:41:49.470 --> 00:41:50.880
And it's not dispositive.

00:41:50.880 --> 00:41:53.802
I'm not saying that
Trump is Hitler.

00:41:53.802 --> 00:41:56.010
But I'm not sure Hitler
wanted to be Hitler when he--

00:41:56.010 --> 00:41:57.480
he just wanted to make America--

00:41:57.480 --> 00:42:00.170
I mean, make Germany great
again and get China and Mexico--

00:42:00.170 --> 00:42:03.320
I mean, get England and
France's boot off his neck.

00:42:03.320 --> 00:42:05.150
You know, and get
rid of the Jews--

00:42:05.150 --> 00:42:06.510
I mean, I'm sorry, the Muslims.

00:42:06.510 --> 00:42:10.320
You know, I mean,
some parallels.

00:42:10.320 --> 00:42:13.080
This is scary stuff.

00:42:13.080 --> 00:42:15.030
Oh, so I went on eBay,
and I bought the book.

00:42:15.030 --> 00:42:17.920
And I now have the
book by my bedside.

00:42:17.920 --> 00:42:20.760
And I haven't read
the actual speeches.

00:42:20.760 --> 00:42:24.060
It's a lot of speeches,
and I'm a real slow reader.

00:42:24.060 --> 00:42:27.000
But the introduction and the
forward, one by a French guy

00:42:27.000 --> 00:42:30.270
and one by a British, the
book came out in 1941.

00:42:30.270 --> 00:42:34.080
And the copy I have, I told this
story last night to a friend

00:42:34.080 --> 00:42:35.590
who said, is it signed?

00:42:35.590 --> 00:42:36.570
Is it autographed?

00:42:36.570 --> 00:42:38.850
No, it's not
autographed by Hitler.

00:42:38.850 --> 00:42:43.310
But the forward and
the introduction

00:42:43.310 --> 00:42:46.110
tackled the question of, as
you read the speeches that

00:42:46.110 --> 00:42:48.480
follow, what is
there about this that

00:42:48.480 --> 00:42:50.730
allowed this man to be
democratically elected

00:42:50.730 --> 00:42:54.050
in 1933, which he was?

00:42:54.050 --> 00:42:56.300
He didn't have 50% of the
vote, but he had enough.

00:42:56.300 --> 00:42:57.870
Neither did Trump.

00:42:57.870 --> 00:42:58.960
He had enough.

00:42:58.960 --> 00:43:04.590
And you read these analyses,
descriptions of his rhetoric

00:43:04.590 --> 00:43:08.580
and his style, and
you say, oh my god.

00:43:08.580 --> 00:43:10.920
And so I took some
of the excerpts

00:43:10.920 --> 00:43:13.970
and put them on my little
blog post thing every day.

00:43:13.970 --> 00:43:15.720
I put them on this
blog post, and I didn't

00:43:15.720 --> 00:43:16.890
say what they were about.

00:43:16.890 --> 00:43:18.848
And everybody assumed I
was writing about Trump

00:43:18.848 --> 00:43:20.280
and that I was taking an ex--

00:43:20.280 --> 00:43:21.590
little bit stilted language.

00:43:21.590 --> 00:43:23.991
Well, yeah, it was from
1941, and they wrote a little

00:43:23.991 --> 00:43:24.490
differently.

00:43:24.490 --> 00:43:26.400
One was British.

00:43:26.400 --> 00:43:28.110
So I don't want to
make too much of that,

00:43:28.110 --> 00:43:33.150
but this is a time like
no other in our history.

00:43:33.150 --> 00:43:37.380
And we may somehow get out
of it and right ourselves

00:43:37.380 --> 00:43:38.910
before too much
more damage is done.

00:43:38.910 --> 00:43:41.670
But an awful lot of damage
has already been done.

00:43:41.670 --> 00:43:44.910
Around the world,
I have no problem.

00:43:44.910 --> 00:43:46.650
China's great.

00:43:46.650 --> 00:43:48.510
Russia would be
lovely if they didn't

00:43:48.510 --> 00:43:51.810
have a journalist-murdering
and autocrat,

00:43:51.810 --> 00:43:53.970
kleptocrat, plutocrat.

00:43:53.970 --> 00:43:55.290
But China's fine.

00:43:55.290 --> 00:43:58.950
But they're picking up the
slack that we're-- we're losing

00:43:58.950 --> 00:44:02.370
our ability to help
lead the world,

00:44:02.370 --> 00:44:04.650
which isn't necessarily
great for us.

00:44:04.650 --> 00:44:06.510
But it's also not
great for the world,

00:44:06.510 --> 00:44:09.450
because the world
needs sober leadership.

00:44:09.450 --> 00:44:19.040
In Barack Obama, I think we
had the most solid, cerebral,

00:44:19.040 --> 00:44:23.100
sensible, wonderful
leader of my lifetime

00:44:23.100 --> 00:44:25.830
and in a long, long time.

00:44:25.830 --> 00:44:28.740
And Clinton, other than a
couple of obvious issues,

00:44:28.740 --> 00:44:30.720
was terrific as well.

00:44:30.720 --> 00:44:32.400
I don't think Bush
was in that league.

00:44:32.400 --> 00:44:35.020
And Trump is in a whole--
it's a whole other ball game.

00:44:35.020 --> 00:44:36.520
This is not American democracy.

00:44:36.520 --> 00:44:38.226
This is a big problem.

00:44:38.226 --> 00:44:40.350
If anybody is brave enough
to ask another question,

00:44:40.350 --> 00:44:41.750
it will be the yes or no answer.

