00:45:45.350 --> 00:45:47.320
ANDY TOBIAS: Well,
it's very gratifying.

00:45:47.320 --> 00:45:49.390
And so this guy from Romania--

00:45:49.390 --> 00:45:51.670
I think only five people
have read it in Romanian.

00:45:51.670 --> 00:45:55.640
I'd love to see it in Spanish
or some other languages.

00:45:55.640 --> 00:45:57.400
And one other thing
to say about that

00:45:57.400 --> 00:46:00.430
is, so I used to get these
wonderful hand-written letters

00:46:00.430 --> 00:46:05.140
or typewritten letters
in the '70s and the '80s.

00:46:05.140 --> 00:46:08.150
You wrote the story of my life,
and all this kind of stuff.

00:46:08.150 --> 00:46:10.682
They were very nice letters.

00:46:10.682 --> 00:46:14.545
And then Amazon was invented,
and it had five stars,

00:46:14.545 --> 00:46:16.510
and it made me feel
really good, or 4 and 1/2,

00:46:16.510 --> 00:46:17.301
or whatever it had.

00:46:17.301 --> 00:46:18.910
It was very nice.

00:46:18.910 --> 00:46:21.250
And then I stopped
looking for a long time.

00:46:21.250 --> 00:46:24.520
And I looked back maybe
10 years ago or something,

00:46:24.520 --> 00:46:26.660
and it was down to three stars.

00:46:26.660 --> 00:46:29.230
And there were all
these one-star reviews.

00:46:29.230 --> 00:46:33.620
And at first, you know,
desperate for love

00:46:33.620 --> 00:46:36.520
before all other
things, I think, oh no.

00:46:36.520 --> 00:46:39.192
This is terrible.

00:46:39.192 --> 00:46:40.900
Basically, they were
saying, what a dick.

00:46:40.900 --> 00:46:42.445
I mean, this guy,
he was a homophobe,

00:46:42.445 --> 00:46:45.380
and he is so impressed
with himself,

00:46:45.380 --> 00:46:48.230
and he's a dreadful person.

00:46:48.230 --> 00:46:50.230
Why do people like this
book and all this stuff?

00:46:50.230 --> 00:46:53.370
And at first I was
a little crushed.

00:46:53.370 --> 00:46:55.870
And then I realized-- maybe
this is just a rationalization--

00:46:55.870 --> 00:46:58.750
but I realized, this is great.

00:46:58.750 --> 00:47:01.521
This is really a wonderful
barometer of how much progress

00:47:01.521 --> 00:47:02.020
we've made.

00:47:02.020 --> 00:47:05.200
Because today's kids cannot--

00:47:05.200 --> 00:47:06.520
I mean, they can process.

00:47:06.520 --> 00:47:07.540
They're real smart.

00:47:07.540 --> 00:47:10.990
But they can't fully grasp
how different the world was.

00:47:10.990 --> 00:47:14.020
And even some of my
peers have forgotten.

00:47:14.020 --> 00:47:17.700
Because now you go back and
you read it, and you think,

00:47:17.700 --> 00:47:19.360
yeah, what a dick.

00:47:19.360 --> 00:47:21.080
But the world was
very different.

00:47:21.080 --> 00:47:21.740
And I agree.

00:47:21.740 --> 00:47:24.310
I was a dick.

00:47:24.310 --> 00:47:25.420
But we evolve.

00:47:25.420 --> 00:47:28.830
And anyway, so the third one,
hopefully people won't think

00:47:28.830 --> 00:47:29.500
I'm--

00:47:29.500 --> 00:47:30.541
