this was not a good idea.

00:51:31.460 --> 00:51:33.650
This was an opportunity
to really build the party

00:51:33.650 --> 00:51:38.490
and build leadership and
do all sorts of things.

00:51:38.490 --> 00:51:43.042
Now we have a really dynamic
chair, who I don't think--

00:51:43.042 --> 00:51:45.500
I mean, his strongest suit is
not TV, which is unfortunate,

00:51:45.500 --> 00:51:47.166
because that's how
most people know him.

00:51:47.166 --> 00:51:49.430
And so Tom Perez, if
you've seen him on TV,

00:51:49.430 --> 00:51:53.720
you hopefully say, guy's got
a lot of fight, which he does.

00:51:53.720 --> 00:51:57.140
And he's smart, and he's for
all the right things, all great.

00:51:57.140 --> 00:52:00.560
Somehow it's not Bill
Clinton's communication skills

00:52:00.560 --> 00:52:01.580
or whatever.

00:52:01.580 --> 00:52:03.480
But he is really good.

00:52:03.480 --> 00:52:06.800
And I got calls from way up
in the Obama administration,

00:52:06.800 --> 00:52:10.970
people saying, of all the
cabinet secretaries we had,

00:52:10.970 --> 00:52:14.769
Tom was either the best or tied
for first with two or three

00:52:14.769 --> 00:52:15.310
other people.

